"
      No Breaks is a pretty unique guild. We value personality as much as skill.
      The majority of our members are adults, but we make a few exceptions for 16yo+. If you are
      interested in joining the raiding team, there is a two week trial period
      to see how everyone gets along. If all goes well, you'll be accepted to
      join the raid team! (We love our casual players, too!)
    "
"The officers are Konnovar, Nebet, Skarelin, Dathunknown, Alasa, Leth, Tumblrderp, Veksaryn, and Shadrn."

"

Current Mythic Recruitment Needs

Tanks: None
Healers: Paladin, Shaman, Druid
Melee DPS: Warrior
Ranged DPS: Hunters
"

"Please head over to our forums to apply. The officers will review your
            application and get back to you. You can also talk to us in-game if you
            would like some more information.
            "
"We require a few addons to make the raiding experience more efficient. They are mandatory."
"We use Mumble. You must have a working headset and microphone to raid. Ask a guildie for the login info."

"
      EPGP is a ratio of Effort Points (EP) and Gear Points (GP).
      Effort points are awarded for a fixed amount for showing up on time, boss kills, and guild contests.
      They may also be taken away for being tardy without notice, absence without notice, rage quitting, etc.
      Gear Points is the score given for your equipped and not-equipped gear.
    "

"
      EPGP is not DKP. You won't be bidding on items. If you roll on an item you want,
      the lootmaster will be able to see all the rolls for said item and compare EPGP ratios.
      The roll with highest effort points vs lowest gear points wins the roll.
      This system ensures fair loot distribution across the raid group to maintain even gear scores.
      The lootmaster does have final say in who wins the item.
    "
"\n      The complete list of EP values can be found here.\n    "

"
      Please post in the forums or on the facebook page if you will be late
      or cannot make your raid time. It gives us time to find a replacement
      for you and saves you from losing EP! We understand life happens sometimes.
    "
"\n      Although we find rage-quitting to be highly entertaining, we prefer it doesn't happen. We're here to have fun!\n    "
" If something happens and you're not having fun, tell us."
" If you need a minute to fix something or take care of real life issues, step out of the raid and come back when you're ready."
" We know progression is rough. Keep your cool."

"
      We require everyone to supply their own flasks, potions, and food. Be prepared!
      If you need help or are able to help others, talk to your guildmates!

When using `ember fastboot --serve-assets` the application output will
already be rendered to the DOM when the actual JavaScript loads. Ember
does not automatically clear its `rootElement` so this leads to the
"double" applications being visible at once (only the "bottom" one is
running via JS and is interactive).
This removes any pre-rendered ember-view elements, so that the booting
application will replace the pre-rendered output
